article.headline: Washington 84, Oregon State 53
article.story:
SEATTLE (AP) -- Cameo Hicks and reserve Breanne Watson each
scored 13 points Thursday night as Washington trounced Oregon State
84-53.

Kayla Burt's half-court shot as time expired in the first half
gave the Huskies a 20-point lead and they were never threatened in
the second half.

Washington (10-14, 6-8 Pac-10) had 11 steals in the first half,
and a season-high 21 overall, as the Huskies snapped a two-game
losing streak.

Perennial UW bench players Angie Jones and Jackie Hollands added
a combined 11 points. In all, the Huskies had nine players who
scored at least five points.

Kim Butler scored 17 points for the Beavers (6-17, 1-12), losers
in seven of their last eight games. Karen Vickery added 15.

Hicks also grabbed a team-high nine rebounds as Washington
controlled the boards.

Shannon Howell, who scored 34 points for the Beavers in their
last meeting with Washington, scored just 10 points on 3-for-14
shooting Thursday night.
